-- McKenzie Discusses U.S. Probe of HSBC Clients With Asian Accounts: Video
-- 
-- 2010-07-07T00:31:48Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-07/mckenzie-discusses-u-s-probe-of-hsbc-clients-with-asian-accounts-video.html

          
          
             Robert McKenzie, an attorney at 
Arnstein & Lehr
in Chicago, talks with Bloomberg's Susan Li about the U.S. 
government's crackdown on offshore tax evasion.    
 The Justice Department is conducting a criminal 
investigation of HSBC Holdings Plc clients who may have failed 
to disclose accounts in India or Singapore to the Internal 
Revenue Service, according to three people familiar with the 
matter. (Source: Bloomberg)  
 Running time 04:42  
 -0- Jul/07/2010 00:31 GMT
  
          
          


  
     
       
     
           
                           
                 
                 
                                       
                                   
               
                        
           
                          July 7 (Bloomberg) -- Robert McKenzie, an attorney at Arnstein & Lehr
in Chicago, talks with Bloomberg's Susan Li about the U.S. government's crackdown on offshore tax evasion.  
     The Justice Department is conducting a criminal investigation of HSBC Holdings Plc clients who may have failed to disclose accounts in India or Singapore to the Internal Revenue Service, according to three people familiar with the matter. (Source: Bloomberg)  
                           

     
